<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n53073c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53073c">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53073c"> 73(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> cad of 9 tongues / philip 9 tongues cut out / evernew tongue</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The skeleton of the story is to the effect that the apostle <mark>Philip&apos;s tongue was cut out nine times by the heathen, and nine times restored</mark>, on which account his name in Heaven is &lsquo;the <mark>Ever-New Tongue</mark>&rsquo;. <small> R.A. Stewart MacAlister, <a name="MSLI" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MSLI"><cite title="source">The Secret Languages of Ireland</cite></a> (Jan 1937) Hisperic, 74</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
